JOHANNESBURG &#8211; South Africa appointed Lieutenant-General Lesetja Mothiba as acting national police commissioner, the presidency said in on Thursday, after the contract of previous acting head ended.South Africa has been without a permanent head of police since President Jacob Zuma suspended Riah Phiyega in 2015 pending an investigation into her role in the 2012 killing of 34 miners by officers during a violent wildcat strike over pay in Marikana on the platinum belt.